
RUNBOOK UNIQUE (copier-coller)

Objectif: faire la collecte, le train et le test sans ambiguite.

==================================================
1) COLLECTE DEMOS EN LOCAL (3 terminaux)
==================================================

Terminal 1
```zsh
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.zsh
source ~/venvs/mujoco_ros/bin/activate
cd /home/luca/Stage_Lirmm/Diffusion-model-isaacsim
python mujoco/teleop/test_UR10e_touch.py
```

Terminal 2
```zsh
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.zsh
source ~/venvs/mujoco_ros/bin/activate
cd /home/luca/Stage_Lirmm/Diffusion-model-isaacsim/ros2_WS
colcon build
source install/setup.zsh
ros2 launch touch_ros2_driver touch_rviz.launch.py
```

Terminal 3
```zsh
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.zsh
source ~/venvs/mujoco_ros/bin/activate
cd /home/luca/Stage_Lirmm/Diffusion-model-isaacsim
python mujoco/tests/test_UR10e_ik_follower.py
```
or 
```zsh
./launch_all
```
==================================================
2) SYNCHRO LOCAL -> SERVEUR
==================================================

Depuis ton PC local (sync minimal, seulement utile pour train):
```bash
cd /home/luca/Stage_Lirmm/Diffusion-model-isaacsim
rsync -avz --progress \
  configs/ \
  data/datasets/ \
  diffusion_policy/ \
  lvogelgesang@mic-gpu1:~/Diffusion-model-isaacsim/
```

Puis connexion serveur:
```bash
ssh lvogelgesang@mic-gpu1
```

==================================================
3) DANS LE SERVEUR: DOCKER + ENV
==================================================

Verifier le GPU libre:
```bash
nvidia-smi
```

Lancer le conteneur (adapte device=0 ou 1 selon GPU libre):
```bash
docker start diffusion-model
docker exec -it diffusion-model bash



docker run -it --gpus '"device=0"' --rm --shm-size=20gb \
  -v ~/Diffusion-model:/workspace -w /workspace \
  continuumio/miniconda3 bash
```

Installer prerequis systeme:
```bash
apt-get update && apt-get install -y build-essential libosmesa6-dev libgl1 libglfw3 patchelf wget
```

Configurer conda solver rapide:
```bash
conda install -y -n base conda-libmamba-solver
conda config --set solver libmamba
```

Forcer mujoco binaire (evite recompilation):
```bash
grep -q 'mujoco==2.3.7' /workspace/diffusion_policy/conda_environment.yaml || \
sed -i '/- dm-control==1.0.9/i \    - mujoco==2.3.7' /workspace/diffusion_policy/conda_environment.yaml
```

Creer/activer env:
```bash
conda env create -f /workspace/diffusion_policy/conda_environment.yaml
conda activate robodiff
```

Fix stack torch (si necessaire):
```bash
for file in /opt/conda/envs/robodiff/lib/python3.9/site-packages/torch/lib/*.so; do
  patchelf --clear-execstack "$file" || true
done
```

Fix versions Python critiques:
```bash
pip install --no-cache-dir huggingface_hub==0.23.0
pip uninstall -y wandb protobuf || true
pip install --no-cache-dir 'protobuf<5' 'wandb>=0.22.3'
```

==================================================
4) LANCER TRAIN (COMMANDE UNIQUE)
==================================================

Copier les configs dans le dossier utilise par Hydra puis lancer:
```bash
cp /workspace/train/*.yaml /workspace/diffusion_policy/config/
cp /workspace/task/*.yaml /workspace/diffusion_policy/config/task/

cd /workspace

export WANDB_DISABLED=true
export PROTOCOL_BUFFERS_PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATION=python

python train.py \
  --config-name=train_e_waste \
  task=e_waste_image \
  task.dataset_path=/workspace/demo_data_20260430_150524.zarr \
  training.resume=False \
  training.device=cuda:0 \
  logging.mode=disabled \
  logging.resume=False
```

Notes:
- Dans Docker, utiliser toujours cuda:0 (meme si host GPU etait 1).
- Le mode W&B est desactive par defaut pour eviter les crashs de login/protobuf.
- `training.num_epochs=100` dans la commande force l'arret a 100 meme si un fichier yaml local est different.

==================================================
5) (OPTION) REACTIVER W&B
==================================================

Si tu veux W&B apres validation du train:
```bash
conda activate robodiff
wandb login --relogin
wandb status

cd /workspace
python train.py --config-name=train_e_waste_transformer \
  task=e_waste_image_transformer \
  task.dataset_path=/workspace/demo_data_20260518_143018.zarr \
  training.device=cuda:0 \
  logging.mode=online \
  logging.resume=False
```

==================================================
6) TEST POLICY AVEC LE DERNIER CHECKPOINT
==================================================

```bash
cd /workspace
CKPT=$(find /workspace/diffusion_policy/data/outputs -type f -name 'latest.ckpt' | sort | tail -n 1)

source /opt/ros/humble/setup.zsh
source ~/venvs/mujoco_ros/bin/activate
python mujoco/tests/test_UR10e_policy_mujoco.py \
  --checkpoint "$CKPT" \
  --device cuda:0
```

Option stable:
```bash
python mujoco/tests/test_UR10e_policy_mujoco.py \
  --checkpoint data/outputs/2026.04.13/12.44.22_train_diffusion_unet_image_e_waste_image/checkpoints/latest.ckpt \
  --device cpu \
  --policy_hz 10 \
  --kp_pos 8 \
  --kp_rot 4 \
  --max_joint_vel 1.0 \
  --alpha_dq 0.15 \
  --reach_tol 0.006 \
  --reach_tol_rot 0.10 \
  --reach_tol_gripper 0.10 \
  --max_waypoint_time 2.0 \
  --gripper_stall_time 0.5
```


netoyer docker
```zsh
cd /workspace
rm -rf ./* .[^.]*
```
dans le serveur pas docker:
```zsh
mkdir -p /auto/lvogelgesang/tmp_ckpt

docker cp diffusion-model:/workspace/data/outputs/2026.05.21/08.07.08_train_diffusion_transformer_e_waste_e_waste_image_transformer/checkpoints/latest.ckpt /auto/lvogelgesang/tmp_ckpt/transformer_moredata.ckpt

docker cp diffusion-model:/workspace/data/outputs/2026.05.06/08.55.26_train_diffusion_unet_image_e_waste_image_transformer/logs.json.txt /auto/lvogelgesang/tmp_ckpt/logs.json.txt
```
dans le pc local:
```zsh
rsync -avzP lvogelgesang@mic-gpu1:/auto/lvogelgesang/tmp_ckpt/transformer_moredata.ckpt\
  /home/luca/Stage_Lirmm/Diffusion-model-isaacsim/data/checkpoints/

rsync -avzP lvogelgesang@mic-gpu1:/auto/lvogelgesang/tmp_ckpt/logs.json.txt \
  /home/luca/Stage_Lirmm/Diffusion-model-isaacsim/data/checkpoints/logs

netoyer :
ssh lvogelgesang@mic-gpu1 'rm -rf /auto/lvogelgesang/tmp_ckpt'
```
